Title : Kollerfjorden
Text : '''Kollerfjorden''' is a bay in [[Haakon VII Land]] at [[Spitsbergen]], [[Svalbard]]. It is located in the inner part of [[Krossfjorden]], at the eastern side. The bay is named after Norwegian topographer Alfred Koller. At the eastern side of Kollerfjorden is the point of [[Speidarneset]], and to the south the bay ends at [[Regnardneset]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://placenames.npolar.no/stadnamn/Kollerfjorden |title=Kollerfjorden (Svalbard) |publisher=[[Norwegian Polar Institute]] |accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref> There are anchoring conditions for vessels both at the north side and the south side of the bay.<ref>{{cite book |title=Arctic Pilot: Sailing directions Svalbard&ndash;Jan Mayen |year=1988 | volume =7 |publisher=The Norwegian Hydrographic Service and The Norwegian Polar Institute |location=Stavanger |language= |isbn=82-90653-06-9 |pages=264&ndash;265}}</ref>

